	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Probably 70% programming 30% optimizing, or maybe even 60% programming, 40% optimizing.
<br />
<br />My game is a slope detecting 8 way scrolling platformer with 2 player simultaneous co-op (that might be removed for speed reasons if I can't optimize everything enough).
<br />
<br />Everything has to be as fast as possible in a game like this or it'll hit lag quite often. I try to get a good feel for how slow each routine can be in a worst case scenario, and use a cycle counting emulator to time it. If it's slower than the goal, I go through it line by line multiple times to see if I can make it faster. If I can't the way it's written, I'll try to replan the logic so that it's faster.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


